data.description: Located on a large lot in a quiet section of the neighborhood, this brick one story ranch has abundant charm. Offering a delightful blend of style, comfort, and versatility, this property boasts a range of appealing features that make it a must-see. This home has 4 bedrooms/2 baths and is nestled within Killearn Estates subdivision near Centerville Road. The tiled front foyer has a coat closet. The Kitchen cabinets go to the ceiling, tons of storage. The nice size eating area in the kitchen has a view of the spacious back yard and a convenient door to the garage.  Roomy closet next to kitchen eating area contains full size  washer and dryer. All the appliances stay.  The airy Family room has a brick wood burning fireplace. The Classic floor plan allows for lots of furniture placement. Separate Living, Dining, and Family Rooms allow for everyone to have their own space.  Spacious master bedroom and private bathroom has a bathtub/shower combo.  The hall bathroom has 2 sinks and a shower/tub. There is a ceiling fan in family room.   House has plenty of storage and no need to put anything in the attic.  The 2 car garage has lots of storage and an exterior door to the back yard and hurricane rated double garage door. There is a concrete driveway.  There are quiet and energy efficient insulated windows throughout.  The spacious back yard mature trees.  The screened in back patio is about 250 square feet and the concrete  pad for your grill is about 150 square feet.   Seller intends to install new roof shingles prior to closing. There is enough crawlspace under the house for subcontractor to move around. Air condition was new in 2011 and windows new in 2010.  House is under bond with pest control. Don't delay in seeing this Killearn Estates gem, you won't be disappointed.
